    <section class="container">
      <h1> Open Online Account </h1>

      <form action="http://localhost:3000/submit" method="POST">
        <h2>Open Online Account </h2>
        <br />

        <label for="Name">Name</label>
        <input type="text" name="Name" id="Name" required />

        <label for="Address">Address</label>
        <input type="text" name="Address" id="Address" required />

        <label for="DateofBirth">DateofBirth</label>
        <input type="date" name="Dateofbirth" id="Dateofbirth" required />

        <label for="acnumber">Phone Number: </label>
        <input type="tel" name="AccountNumber" id="number" required minlength="10" maxlength="10" placeholder="Enter 10 digits only"/>

        <label for="email">E-mail address</label>
        <input type="email" name="email" id="email" required />

        <label for="password">Password (min 6 characters)</label>
        <input type="password" name="password" id="password" required minlength="6"  />

        <div class="checkboxterms">
          <input
            type="checkbox"
            id="terms"
            name="terms"
            value="terms"
            required
          />
          <label for="terms"> I accept the Terms & Conditions</label>
        </div>
        <button type="submit">Create an account</button>
      </form>

      <section class="faq">
        <h3>Frequently Asked Questions</h3>

        <section class="accordion">
          <div class="question" id="section1">What we do?</div>
          <div class="answer">
            <p>
              As a bank, we provide a wide range of financial services to help individuals, businesses, and organizations manage their money. Our services include saving and checking accounts, loans, mortgages, credit cards, investment options, and financial advice. We also facilitate secure transactions, both locally and internationally, through digital banking, ATMs, and customer service. Our goal is to help you grow, protect, and manage your financial well-being
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="question" id="section2">Who is world bank for?</div>
          <div class="answer">
            <p>
              This bank serves individuals, businesses, and organizations, offering personal banking, loans, and investment services. We help manage finances, provide credit, and facilitate secure transactions. Our goal is to support financial growth and stability for all.
             </p>
          </div>

          <div class="question" id="section3">How much does it cost to open an account?</div>
          <div class="answer">
            <p>
              The cost to open an account can vary depending on the type of account and the bankâ€™s policies. For most basic checking and savings accounts, there may be no initial fee to open an account, but some banks require a minimum deposit. Other account types, like premium or business accounts, might have higher minimum balance requirements or fees. It's best to check with the bank for specific details on fees, minimum deposits, and any ongoing costs associated with the account.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="question" id="section4">
            When do you provide services?
          </div>
          <div class="answer">
            <p>
              Our services are typically available during business hours, which are usually from 9 AM to 5 PM, Monday through Friday. Many banks also offer extended hours through ATMs, online banking, and mobile apps, allowing access to account management and transactions 24/7. Some services may be available on weekends, depending on the branch.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>
      </section>
    </section>

    <script>
    function toggle() {
      this.classList.toggle("active");
    }
    
    // Selects an HTML element, and calls a function which will be executed when the element is clicked.
    document.getElementById("section1").onclick = toggle;
    document.getElementById("section2").onclick = toggle;
    document.getElementById("section3").onclick = toggle;
    document.getElementById("section4").onclick = toggle;
